{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17592676","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17592676"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T10:18:44+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T10:18:44+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15272"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15272","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15272"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.77,0.03,0.13,0.03,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7963"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66612"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7963","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7963"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15272"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52065"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"6910"},{"type":"tags","id":"8745"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19380"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19383"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21394"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66612","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66612"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA histological specimen shows the presence of Brunner glands, which secrete bicarbonate ions and pepsinogen II.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following anatomical regions contains these glands?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Duodenum","Jejunum","Ileum","Distal colon","Proximal colon"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eduodenum\u003C/strong\u003E is the only part of the gastrointestinal tract that contains Brunner glands. These submucosal glands are not found in the \u003Cstrong\u003Eileum\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003Ejejunum\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003Edistal colon\u003C/strong\u003E, or \u003Cstrong\u003Eproximal colon\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBrunner glands secrete an alkaline fluid containing bicarbonate and pepsinogen II. The bicarbonate helps neutralise acidic chyme from the stomach, protecting the duodenal mucosa. This protective function is important as the duodenum is the first part of the small intestine to receive acidic contents from the stomach.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Brunner glands are located exclusively in the duodenum and secrete bicarbonate and pepsinogen II","Brunner glands help protect the duodenal mucosa from acidic chyme entering from the stomach"],"references":["Nightingale, J. M. (2012). Applied anatomy and physiology of the gastrointestinal tract (GIT). Gastrointestinal Tract Imaging E-Book: Gastrointestinal Tract Imaging E-Book, 45.","Podolsky, D. K., Camilleri, M., Fitz, J. G., Kalloo, A. N., Shanahan, F., \u0026 Wang, T. C. (Eds.). (2015). Yamada\u0027s textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons.","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52065"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15272"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52065","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52065"},"attributes":{"cr